Global Transcutaneous Bilirubin Meters Market Insights
Transcutaneous Bilirubin Meters Market size was valued at USD 0.3 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 0.5 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Transcutaneous Bilirubin Meters Market Overview
The global Transcutaneous Bilirubin Meters Market was valued at approximately USD 98.58 million in 2023 and is projected to reach USD 116.34 million by 2029, exhibiting a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 2.80% during the forecast period. These devices are essential for non-invasive monitoring of bilirubin levels, particularly in neonatal care settings. The market's growth is driven by the increasing prevalence of neonatal jaundice and the rising demand for non-invasive diagnostic tools. However, challenges such as variability in measurement accuracy and high equipment costs may impact market expansion. Source

